---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About me" description="Who I am, how I think, and why this site exists.">
  <article class="container narrow about">
    <header class="reveal visible">
      <h1>About me</h1>
      <p class="page-sub">Who I am, how I think, and why this place exists.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose">
      <h2>Who I am</h2>
      <p>
        I'm Oscar. I build things — some for work, others out of my own fire. I'm interested in how
        things work, but I'm more interested in <em>why</em> we make them.
      </p>
      <p>
        <!-- ✏️ Edit this paragraph with your real story: where you're from, what you do, what brought you here. -->
        This paragraph is waiting for your real story. Write it in your own voice — this page is
        your manifesto, not your résumé.
      </p>

      <h2>How I think</h2>
      <ul class="principles">
        <li>
          <strong>Depth before reach.</strong> I'd rather have ten readers who stay than a thousand
          who scroll past.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>I'd rather be found.</strong> I don't go out shouting for attention; I leave true
          things where people can find them.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Building &gt; opining.</strong> Opinions are worth more when they come from
          someone who makes things.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Curiosity as the engine.</strong> The best projects I've made started with a
          "what if...?".
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why this site exists</h2>
      <p>
        For a while I wondered whether having my own site instead of posting on social media was an
        elegant way of hiding. I concluded it isn't — as long as I don't keep it a secret.
      </p>
      <p>
        Social media is a public square: anyone walks by, judges, or ignores. This site is my
        house: whoever arrives, arrives because they meant to. What lasts lives here — my
        philosophy, my projects, my developed opinions. Social media will be the street that leads
        here.
      </p>
      <p>
        I don't want to be a hidden flame. That's why this site has a mascot: a little being of
        simple strokes, alive and in plain sight — proof that what was hidden is now visible.
        <a href="/en/blog/lighting-the-flame/">The full story is in the first post.</a>
      </p>

      <h2>What I like</h2>
      <p>
        <!-- ✏️ Replace with your real tastes: music, books, games, food, quirks. -->
        A list waiting to be written: the music I can't let go of, the books that marked me, the
        ideas I collect. (Oscar: this is your space to be specific — specific is what connects.)
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .about {
    padding: 3.5rem 1.4rem;
  }

  .page-sub {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .prose h2 {
    margin-top: 2.2em;
  }

  .prose p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .prose strong {
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .principles {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.9rem;
  }

  .principles li {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1rem 1.3rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    transition: border-color 0.25s ease, transform 0.25s var(--ease-spring);
  }

  .principles li:hover {
    border-color: var(--border-hover);
    transform: translateX(4px);
  }
</style>
